   <li class="comment byuser comment-author-natsfan even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-59210">
       <div class="commentInfo">Posted by: natsfan &#124; 12/18/10 &#124; 3:48 pm &#124; </div>
       <div id="comment-59210">
                      <div class="commentText"><p>As someone else said, it won&#8217;t happen.  Competition among wireless companies is pretty stiff.  If, say, Verizon were to do this in the USA (or AT&amp;T), you can bet Sprint or TMobile or US Cellular would be salivating at the chance to pick up unhappy Verizon customers.</p>
</div>
